{"type":"system","subtype":"task_started","task_id":"a64fe38e2fca802cf","tool_use_id":"toolu_011dVkNoYbCNwL2ozhAMzvL2","description":"Cross-iteration contradiction check","task_type":"local_agent","prompt":"I need you to check for cross-iteration contradictions in improvement plans for a title extraction system. \n\nRead the improvement plans from iterations 20-25 (the most recent before the current iteration 26):\n- tools/title-loop/docs/20-3b20209/improvement-plan.md\n- tools/title-loop/docs/21-f1e3c51/improvement-plan.md\n- tools/title-loop/docs/22-480d364/improvement-plan.md\n- tools/title-loop/docs/23-6e2e2a7/improvement-plan.md\n- tools/title-loop/docs/24-b15aa30/improvement-plan.md\n- tools/title-loop/docs/25-2331e30/improvement-plan.md\n\nThen compare them against the current iteration 26 plan at:\n- tools/title-loop/docs/26-e8ee23c/improvement-plan.md\n\nLook for cases where iteration 26 proposes changes that CONTRADICT or REVERSE changes made in earlier iterations. Common patterns:\n1. Changing a heuristic in one direction when a previous iteration changed it the other way\n2. Removing or weakening a rule that was specifically added to fix a known failure\n3. Adjusting thresholds or weights that were tuned in a previous iteration without acknowledging those cases\n\nAlso check iterations 15-19 if you find any relevant overlapping areas (OCR repair, section labels, spillover handling, first-after-preamble bonus, isTitleAbsentPage):\n- tools/title-loop/docs/15-b8dddbe/improvement-plan.md\n- tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md\n- tools/title-loop/docs/17-9e42f14/improvement-plan.md\n- tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md\n- tools/title-loop/docs/19-55b161b/improvement-plan.md\n\nFor each contradiction found, report:\n1. What iteration 26 proposes\n2. What the earlier iteration did and why\n3. Whether the two are actually in tension or if 26's proposal is safe\n4. If in tension, what resolution would handle BOTH cases\n\nBe thorough but focused - only report genuine contradictions, not superficial similarities.","uuid":"8ddd197b-7864-40db-a173-dc82ba1f426a","session_id":"18f2edd5-ecb4-45b8-8e46-36d66db82038"}
